      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why don\u0027t we swap Mixers\u0027 lerp convention to A*t + B*(1-t)?  That\u0027ll make MakeLerp() line up with MakeBlend() a little more intuitively; when lerping is used with things that are src-y and dst-y, it\u0027s usually src*t + dst*(1-t).  And then this impl here will become straightforward enough to not need the note.",
      "revId": "5a0c81942d124f0efadf532d13974165e0f32a30",
