      "writtenOn": "2019-03-15T19:13:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Our own lerp impl code is \n\nlerp(a, b, t) : return a(1 - t) + b*t\n\nI find that very readable, since a, b reads in the same order as 0...1 (i.e. it returns a when t is 0).\n\nIf you think this is not as intuitive as a public convention, we should think more. If this comment is about my swizzling as the impl, that can be fixed (in several ways probably). One obvious change could be that I defined mixers in the pipeline to be Mixer(dr,dg,db,da,    r,g,b,a). That would align with our current lerp stage.\n\nOn the Blend front, I see that I picked the opposite param order from other helpers like SkShader::MakeCompose(dst, src, mode). I agree I should match that in the Blend Mixer...",
      "parentUuid": "70353bf4_274060c8",
